cancelOwnershipHandover().details: Cancels the two-step ownership handover to the caller, if any.

completeOwnershipHandover(address).details: Allows the owner to complete the two-step ownership handover to `pendingOwner`. Reverts if there is no existing ownership handover requested by `pendingOwner`.

returns._0: The maximum amount of rewards that can be claimed by the protocol or the quest deployer

owner().details: Returns the owner of the contract.

ownershipHandoverExpiresAt(address).details: Returns the expiry timestamp for the two-step ownership handover to `pendingOwner`.

ownershipHandoverValidFor().details: Returns how long a two-step ownership handover is valid for in seconds.

pause().details: Only the owner of the Quest can call this function. Also requires that the Quest has started (not by date, but by calling the start function)

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

queue().details: Requires that the balance of the rewards in the contract is greater than or equal to the maximum amount of rewards that can be claimed by all users and the protocol

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the owner to renounce their ownership.

requestOwnershipHandover().details: Request a two-step ownership handover to the caller. The request will be automatically expire in 48 hours (172800 seconds) by default.

singleClaim(address).details: transfers rewards to the account, can only be called once per account per quest and only by the quest factory

params.account_: The account to transfer rewards to

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the owner to transfer the ownership to `newOwner`.

unPause().details: Only the owner of the Quest can call this function. Also requires that the Quest has started (not by date, but by calling the start function)

withdrawRemainingTokens().details: Function that transfers all 1155 tokens and ETH in the contract to the owner

maxProtocolReward().notice: Function that gets the maximum amount of rewards that can be claimed by the protocol or the quest deployer

queue().notice: Queues the quest by marking it ready to start at the contract level. Marking a quest as queued does not mean that it is live. It also requires that the start time has passed

withdrawRemainingTokens().notice: This function can only be called after the quest end time.
